FBIS3-14674 "drnes061_n_94004" FBIS-NES-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 LEBANON Israeli Raids on Iqlim al-Tuffah Noted NC3003111494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 30 Mar 94 NC3003111494 Beirut Radio Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] We have been informed that at 1320, Israel raided the Iqlim al-Tuffah heights. Israeli warplanes are now releasing thermal balloons. After 1300, residential areas in 'Arab Salim started coming under heavy sniper fire from the occupation troops' posts in al-Suwayda'. Israeli warplanes continue to overfly al-Nabatiyah and Iqlim al-Tuffah, drawing ground fire. Since 1200, Israeli warplanes have been flying over al-Nabatiyah and Iqlim al- Tuffah and conducting mock raids. They drew antiaircraft fire from the Lebanese Army's ground defenses. [In a related report, Paris AFP in English at 1038 GMT on 30 March adds the following: "Two Israeli warplanes blasted positions of the pro-Iranian Hizballah movement in south Lebanon in two successive waves on Wednesday, police here said. ["The warplanes fired two missiles at positions in the Iqlim al- Tuffah hills east of the port city of Sidon, where Hizballah maintains strongholds dug in the rock."]
